Hey there! I’m Umang Utkarsh, a recent graduate from the National Institute of Technology, Karnataka, India, with a B.Tech degree. My journey in the tech world has been quite an adventure, starting during my college days with a keen interest in machine learning projects.

After graduating in 2023, I started my professional journey as a Software Development Engineer at Jio Platforms Limited. Here, I’ve had the opportunity to dive deep into various technologies and frameworks. Currently, my role involves working with Golang for backend development, Kubernetes for container orchestration Openshift for managing containerised applications, and Next.js.

My toolkit is quite diverse and includes HTML, CSS, JavaScript, ReactJS, NodeJS, MongoDB, SQL, Redux. On the programming side, I’m proficient in C++, JavaScript, Golang, Python, and TypeScript. During my college days, I worked on several projects using the MERN stack and dabbled in Angular for some beginner-level projects.

Coming from a non-tech background, I’ve always been driven by curiosity and a passion for learning. I’ve independently navigated the tech domain, and this self-driven exploration has been incredibly rewarding. My foray into open-source software began after college, and it has been an exhilarating experience. Contributing to open-source communities not only allows me to give back but also continuously challenges me to improve and innovate.

At Jio Platforms Limited, I’ve faced many challenges, but these have only fueled my passion for technology. The exposure to different technologies and frameworks has been both challenging and rewarding. I firmly believe that Rocket.Chat, with its alignment to my tech stack, offers a platform for continuous learning and growth. Being part of such an incredible open-source software community is something I look forward to, as it resonates with my journey and aspirations.

In my free time, I love exploring new technologies, working on personal projects, and contributing to open-source. My passion for tech goes beyond just coding; it’s about creating, innovating, and making a difference in the tech community.

position: I am a web developer with a passion for AI and Embedded Systems, currently in the final stretch of my studies at IIIT Kottayam. This year, I’ve channeled my skills into GSoC '24 with Rocket.Chat, climbing to the top of the leaderboard. long_biography:
As a final-year student at IIIT Kottayam, my path has been an exciting mix of web development, AI, and embedded systems. After completing my DSA and placements, I wanted a fresh challenge and found open source.

My Rocket.Chat story began with a struggle to set it up on Windows, but I finally got it running on Linux. My first contribution was fixing a bug in the MultiSelect component. My first pull request was rejected, but I didn’t give up. I kept working on issues, fixing bugs, and helping others, which helped me earn a good reputation.

I made friends with other developers and worked on projects like EmbeddedChat and RC apps, such as Apps.Notion. My hard work paid off, and I became a top contributor. When GSoC came around, I eagerly submitted proposals for three Rocket.Chat projects, including Embedded Chat 2024.

After a tense wait, I got the acceptance email for Embedded Chat 2024 on May 1st, starting a new and exciting chapter in my open source journey.

Currently, I'm pursuing a B.Tech degree in Computer Science, a path that has allowed me to explore a diverse range of technical disciplines and hone my skills as a full-stack developer.
One of the highlights of my academic journey was the opportunity to intern as a DevOps Engineer at Zscaler. This experience exposed me to the world of infrastructure automation and development workflow optimization, instilling in me a growing passion for DevOps practices. I thrived on the challenge of automating unit test case generation and improving the overall test coverage with the help of a custom-built VS Code extension and an internal language model. As a testament to the success of my project, I had the honor of presenting it to the board of Zscaler, an experience that further fueled my enthusiasm for solving complex problems and delivering tangible results.
Alongside my academic and professional pursuits, I've become an active contributor to the open-source community. My love for problem-solving and creative thinking has driven me to explore various open-source projects, where I've had the chance to collaborate with like-minded individuals, learn from their expertise, and contribute my own unique perspectives.
